	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				The avengers seem to be a random spawn and always spawn either just after or within 30 seconds or so of killing the chief.  Most people do not get a chance to con them as we die way too fast. <BR>
<BR>
The best thing to do is make sure all have sow, when they spawn, make a break for the CC zone (outside the main building and to the left.  I would advise that no one be camping just outside the cc zone.  I also advise (and do this myself) that any groups hunting the chief give an /ooc when killing him and when he is just about to die so that people will be warned.  <BR>
<BR>
The avengers go after the group(s) or people involved in killing the chief first, then they just aggro anyone else within range.  They will de-spawn (disappear) after about 5 mins or so.  They do see through invis and are always fast.  <BR>
<BR>
I am going to attempt to arrange a guild event to take them down so hopefully should be able to post some post-death (avengers, that is) information.<BR>
<BR>
Tybel Bonaparte<BR>
Proud Gnome Enchanter<BR>
The Tribunal<BR>
<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

